<br>
Seriously, maxed out Cleric melee is about 40 DPS.  Add in crits and you get about 49 DPS (FoM3) for the grand total of 30 AA points. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aumnyder>Aumnyder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/19/03 1:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=162.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cleric AA points - a practical application</span><hr size=1> 30 AA pts? I put 2 in SCF 1 to get Venerable and move along. I was merely pointing out that it was fun to see crits from a summoned hammer proc. Sometimes the game is about having fun and not about supercomputer computations of the relative merits of various damage ratios etc etc. <br>
 <p><center>Aumnyder, High Elf, Cleric of Tunare<br>Member of House Valiant<br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=779689" target="_new">My Equipment</a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elhanamistfall>ElhanaMistfall</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.mistfits.com/tgrobb/elhanaportsmall.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Hospital with a pony tail</span><br>  Posts: 348<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/19/03 3:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=162.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.mistfits.com/tgrobb/elhanatoonsmall.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cleric AA points - a practical application</span><hr size=1> Don't take people too seriously if they try to tell you to learn your AA skills in a certain order or that some are purely useless. When it comes down to it, none of them are useless; some might have a more practical application than others, but in essence they all give you something you didn't have before.<br>
<br>
I have spellcasting fury 1, and before I head on to level 61 I plan on completing Spellcasting Fury 3 as well as a few other skills. If you get a fair number of chances to jump in with your hammer, or you get to spend a bit of time nuking, you will likely come to greatly enjoy Spellcasting Fury. I was delighted the other day in Maiden's Eye when I landed two crit nukes in a row. Oh, it certainly doesn't change the game (and few AAs will do that, honestly - with perhaps the exception of Spellcasting Mastery 3) but it does make it more fun.<br>
<br>
The game is *not* about DPS and formulas. It's about having fun. It's a game, not a science =)<br>
